        <tr style="background:#f9fafb;"><td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">Bean throwing</td><td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">節分 (setsubun)</td><td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">February 3</td><td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ddd;">Throw beans shouting 鬼は外、福は内 (out with demons, in with luck)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p>Winter vocabulary centers on warmth and celebration: こたつ (kotatsu, heated table with blanket), 鍋 (nabe, hot pot), 温泉 (onsen, hot spring), 雪 (yuki, snow), 年越しそば (toshikoshi soba, year-crossing noodles eaten on December 31), and お年玉 (otoshidama, New Year money gift for children).</p>

